HEADWORD: Stentorophonic
<hw>Sten`to*ro*phon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
Stentor + <?/ a sound, voice. See <er>Stentor</er>.]</ety> <def>Speaking
or sounding very loud; stentorian.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of this <qex>stentorophonic</qex> horn of Alexander there is a
preserved in the Vatican.</q> <rj><qau>Derham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

